llion).\nIn July 2003, the company acquired Cobalt Media who added their portfolio to that of Winchester's. In March 2004, the company was taken over by ContentFilms Inc and the name was officially changed from Winchester Films to ContentFilm. ContentFilm is no longer listed on the AIM market in London.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-09-06T02:18:48.722761+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5363, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Winchester_Films"}], "uuid": "a2771a86-a55d-4bba-a653-b044e4e8ac88", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "4018", "external_references": [{"id": 25298, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q8023804"}, {"id": 32045, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "307477407"}, {"id": 32046, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "ns2014001432"}, {"id": 32047, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-ns2014001432"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T02:18:48.732551+10:00"}, {"id": 34491, "name": "William Sassoon", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2219093, "title": "English without tears", "work_id": 94733, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1996668, "title": "The Girl on a motorcycle = La Motocyclette", "work_id": 92791, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T16:13:18.402815+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "2d6439ff-1b88-4cee-acef-2bc3e91c55b9", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "30493", "external_references": [{"id": 35765, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121315174"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T02:18:00.538330+10:00"}, {"id": 34487, "name": "Satoshi Kon", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2196462, "title": "Perfect blue", "work_id": 92780, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "1963-10-12", "date_of_death": "2010-08-24", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [{"id": 2, "name": "Japanese", "slug": "japanese"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 8, "name": "Japan", "slug": "japan"}], "biography": "Satoshi Kon (今 敏, Kon Satoshi, October 12, 1963 – August 24, 2010) was a Japanese film director, animator, screenwriter and manga artist from Sapporo, Hokkaido and a member of the Japanese Animation Creators Association (JAniCA). He was a graduate of the Graphic Design department of the Musashino Art University. He is best known for his acclaimed anime films Perfect Blue (1997), Millennium Actress (2001), Tokyo Godfathers (2003), and Paprika (2006), and the TV series Paranoia Agent (2004).\nHe died of pancreatic cancer at the age of 46 on August 24, 2010.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T17:00:49.449629+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 5128, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satoshi_Kon"}], "uuid": "cf410da9-cc57-4567-9dde-de83ffe6a4af", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "28605", "external_references": [{"id": 25637, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q333643"}, {"id": 31423, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "46968186"}, {"id": 31424, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no2004097153"}, {"id": 31425, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no2004097153"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-06T01:07:04.827169+10:00"}, {"id": 34486, "name": "Takeshi Washitani", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2196461, "title": "Perfect blue", "work_id": 92780, "role": "producer", "role_id": 1089, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of